                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant vermillion and vivid vermillion for
                           the names in the supplication formulas)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS13367ZawaldaGarima">Zawalda Garimā</persName>
                        is mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#43vb">43vb</locus> and
                        52vb (here he is mentioned as ʾabbā Walda Garimā).
                        <date>19th century
                           (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰላ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡ </expan> (in Text III)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; names of the donors; name of the
                           protagonist (both Libānos and Maṭāʿ); in Text I, groups of lines on the
                           incipit page of the prologue (fol. 3r) and on the incipit page of the
                           proper account (fol. 17r), and the incipit of some subsections; in Text
                           II, groups of lines on the incipit page, and incipit of each miracle; in
                           Text III, groups of lines on the incipit page and the word salām (and its
                           abbreviation); elements of the punctuation signs, text dividers; elements
                           of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     
                     <seg type="script">Despite the recent age, there are two
                        ancient
                        features:
                       (1) - the letter ጵ in the word ኢትዮጵያ has
                        the 6th order marker set up on the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to
                        the left (e.g. <locus target="#6va">6va</locus>, 6vb, 11va,
                        12va)
                        (2) - the crux ansata with coronis on
                           <locus target="#14v">14v</locus>.</seg></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
